Rating: 4
Great recipe, but I have a nice twist. I have made this many times and it is always a crowd pleaser. My best however was to replace the lamb shanks with lean stew beef (sirloin tip), add cubed yams and one additional cup of wine. It turns out a bit different as the yams break down a bit and create a puree broth, but it was really great. This base recipe works for just about any slow cook meat.

Rating: 3
I made this recipe this evening to great reviews from my husband. I agree it was quite good. I followed the recipe as stated with only a couple of deviations; 1. I added about 1tsp of sugar to counter the acidity of the wine and tomatoes. 2. I simmered the shanks for 2 hours. The shanks came out so tender you did not need a knife, it came right off the bone! I served this over mashed potatoes which was a lovely combo. This was an easy and tasty recipe that is definitely a keeper!

