Delicious. I had to make a few changes due to what I had in the pantry. I reconstituted dried shitaki in boiling water for 45 mins and used that sliced up instead of the porcini. I also skipped the carrots and used dried parsley. I subbed 1/2 of the mushroom water and 1/2 rice wine for the dry red. Still came out wonderful. Also, I had to cook my shanks for a good 45 minutes longer than the recipe stated to get it to that falling off the bone perfect stage.

